Notes:

    Common commands

        pwd
        mkdir
        cd
        cd ..
        cd ~ (home)
        touch
        ls
        ls -l 
        ls -la
        rm
        rm -r <folder>
        rm -rf <folder>
        clear
        code <filename> (opens in vscode)

    Installing Git

        $ brew install git

        $ sudo apt-get update
        $ sudo apt-get install

    Configure git

        $ git config --global user.name "Leon Noel" 
        $ git config --global user.email "leon@leonnoel.com"

    Basic git commands

        $ git init
        $ git add <file>
        $ git add *.html (all html files)
        $ git add .
        $ git status
        $ git rm --cached <file> (remove file from staging area)
        $ git commit (opens vim)
        $ git commit -m "message"
        $ git branch -M main (change name of staging area to main)
        $ git branch <name> (create new branch)
        $ git checkout <name> (move to branch)
        $ git merge <branch>

